<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900419-0103</DOCNO><DOCID>900419-0103.</DOCID><HL>   Conversion Industries Venture</HL><DATE>04/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   PCG CVD</CO><LP>   PASADENA, Calif. -- Conversion Industries Inc., anindependent power-production company, said it agreed to builda $50 million oil-recovery facility and cogeneration powerplant in Kern County, Calif., in a joint venture with EnergyReserve Inc. of Phoenix, Ariz.   At full production, the oil-recovery facility is expectedto produce about 2,500 barrels of oil a day, Conversion said.Project construction is expected to begin next month. Allelectric power will be sold to San Francisco-based PacificGas andamp; Electric Co.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>